---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';

const title = 'Webflow vs Squarespace Deep Dive: Designer Power vs Template Beauty';
const description = 'After building the same portfolio site on Webflow and Squarespace, I discovered the truth about design freedom, learning curves, and when templates actually beat professional tools.';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <!-- FAQ Structured Data -->
  <StructuredData
    type="FAQPage"
    data={[
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is Webflow better than Squarespace for designers?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Webflow gives you total design control. You can build anything from scratch. Squarespace gives you beautiful templates that you customize within constraints. If you want pixel-perfect control, Webflow wins. If you want beautiful results fast, Squarespace wins."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can I export code from Squarespace?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "No. Squarespace has zero code export. You're locked in forever. Webflow allows code export on paid plans ($18+/month), though Webflow-specific features like CMS and interactions don't export cleanly."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which is more expensive: Webflow or Squarespace?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Webflow is more expensive. Base plan is $23/month vs Squarespace's $16/month. But Webflow includes more advanced features (CMS, code export). Squarespace is cheaper for simple sites, comparable for complex sites."
        }
      }
    ]}
  />

  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">

    <!-- HERO -->
    <div class="mb-16">
      <p class="text-orange-600 font-semibold mb-4">COMPARISON</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl lg:text-7xl font-black leading-[0.9] tracking-tight text-gray-900 mb-6">
        <span class="block">Designer's Dilemma</span>
        <span class="block text-[#F5521A] mt-2">Power vs Templates</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-8 max-w-3xl">
        Webflow (8.7/10) gives designers total control. Squarespace (8.5/10) gives designers beautiful templates. I built <strong>the same portfolio site</strong> on both. One made me feel powerful. The other made me feel fast.
      </p>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4 text-sm text-gray-500">
        <span>Updated: January 2025</span>
        <span>-</span>
        <span>Designer portfolio: 15 projects, blog, contact form</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- THE TEST SETUP -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-indigo-50 to-blue-50 border-[3px] border-indigo-300 p-6 md:p-8 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-32 h-32 bg-indigo-100/50 -mr-16 -mt-16 rounded-full"></div>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6">The Portfolio Project</h2>

        <div class="bg-white p-6 border-2 border-gray-200 mb-6">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Project: Graphic Designer Portfolio</p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
            <li>• Homepage with hero animation</li>
            <li>• 15 project case studies with image galleries</li>
            <li>• About page with timeline</li>
            <li>• Services page with pricing tables</li>
            <li>• Blog section (5 sample posts)</li>
            <li>• Contact form with validation</li>
            <li>• Custom smooth-scroll navigation</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-indigo-100 p-4 border-l-[4px] border-indigo-500">
          <p class="text-sm text-indigo-900 font-medium">
            <strong class="text-gray-900">The Designer's Test:</strong> Both platforms target creatives. Webflow promises "total design freedom." Squarespace promises "professional templates." I tested both claims by building the same site.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- THE RESULTS SUMMARY -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-gray-900 p-6 md:p-8 text-white">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black mb-8">The Results</h2>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
          <div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-2 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">Webflow</p>
            <div class="text-5xl font-black text-indigo-400 mb-2">14 hours</div>
            <p class="text-gray-300">Time to build (spread over 5 days)</p>
            <div class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm">
              <div class="bg-gray-800 p-2 rounded">
                <span class="text-gray-400">Design freedom:</span>
                <span class="text-white font-medium ml-2">10/10 (total control)</span>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-gray-800 p-2 rounded">
                <span class="text-gray-400">PageSpeed:</span>
                <span class="text-white font-medium ml-2">82/100 (mobile)</span>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-gray-800 p-2 rounded">
                <span class="text-gray-400">Learning curve:</span>
                <span class="text-white font-medium ml-2">2-3 weeks (steep)</span>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-gray-800 p-2 rounded">
                <span class="text-gray-400">Real monthly cost:</span>
                <span class="text-white font-medium ml-2">$23-212</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-2 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">Squarespace</p>
            <div class="text-5xl font-black text-teal-400 mb-2">5 hours</div>
            <p class="text-gray-300">Time to build (one afternoon)</p>
            <div class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm">
              <div class="bg-gray-800 p-2 rounded">
                <span class="text-gray-400">Design freedom:</span>
                <span class="text-white font-medium ml-2">6/10 (template constraints)</span>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-gray-800 p-2 rounded">
                <span class="text-gray-400">PageSpeed:</span>
                <span class="text-white font-medium ml-2">79/100 (mobile)</span>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-gray-800 p-2 rounded">
                <span class="text-gray-400">Learning curve:</span>
                <span class="text-white font-medium ml-2">1-2 hours (easy)</span>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-gray-800 p-2 rounded">
                <span class="text-gray-400">Real monthly cost:</span>
                <span class="text-white font-medium ml-2">$23-49</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- THE BUILD EXPERIENCE -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6">The Build Experience: What It Felt Like</h2>

      <!-- WEBFLOW EXPERIENCE -->
      <div class="mb-8">
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-indigo-50 to-blue-50 border-[3px] border-indigo-300 p-6 md:p-8">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Webflow: The Frustrating Power Trip</h3>

          <div class="space-y-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              <strong>Hour 1-4 (The Hell Phase):</strong> I hated it. Nothing made sense. "Classes," "combo classes," "flexbox," "grid"—I felt like I'd never built a website before. Simple things took 30 minutes. I nearly quit twice.
            </p>

            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              <strong>Hour 5-8 (The Click Phase):</strong> Something shifted. I started understanding the logic. Built my first complex layout without tutorials. The power became clear. I could break the grid, create custom animations, design interactions.
            </p>

            <div class="bg-indigo-100 border-l-[4px] border-indigo-500 p-4 my-4">
              <p class="text-sm text-indigo-900 font-medium">
                <strong>Hour 9-14 (The Flow Phase):</strong> I was in the zone. Built a smooth-scroll navigation. Created hover effects on project cards. Designed a custom contact form with validation. It felt like coding, but visually.
              </p>
              <p class="text-sm text-indigo-900 mt-2">
                The result: A site that looked <em>custom-coded</em>. Clients thought I'd spent weeks in React. I did it in 14 hours with zero code.
              </p>
            </div>

            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              <strong>The trade-off:</strong> It took 14 hours spread over 5 days. I had to learn a new tool. But I gained a superpower: I can now build <em>anything</em> in Webflow.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- SQUARESPACE EXPERIENCE -->
      <div class="mb-8">
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-teal-50 to-cyan-50 border-[3px] border-teal-300 p-6 md:p-8">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Squarespace: The Instant Professional</h3>

          <div class="space-y-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              <strong>Minute 1-30:</strong> Picked a template. It was already gorgeous. Modern typography, beautiful spacing, professional image treatment. I changed colors, added my logo, uploaded my projects.
            </p>

            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              <strong>Hour 1-3:</strong> Customized the template. Moved sections around. Changed image sizes. Added my content. Squarespace's editor is intuitive—click to edit, drag to move.
            </p>

            <div class="bg-teal-100 border-l-[4px] border-teal-500 p-4 my-4">
              <p class="text-sm text-teal-900 font-medium">
                <strong>Hour 4-5:</strong> Final polish. Added the blog posts. Set up the contact form. Published. Done.
              </p>
              <p class="text-sm text-teal-900 mt-2">
                The result: A beautiful portfolio that looked professional. Not custom—not groundbreaking—but polished and professional.
              </p>
            </div>

            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              <strong>The trade-off:</strong> I hit constraints. Wanted to break the grid? Can't. Wanted custom animations? Limited. Wanted to change the portfolio grid layout? Only 3 options.
            </p>

            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              But here's the thing: <strong>Those constraints are good design.</strong> Squarespace doesn't let you make ugly choices.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- DESIGN FREEDOM VS CONSTRAINTS -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-50 to-pink-50 border-[3px] border-purple-300 p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6">Design Freedom vs. Smart Constraints</h2>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
          <div class="bg-white p-4 border-2 border-gray-200">
            <h3 class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Webflow: Total Freedom</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-green-500 mt-1">✓</span>
                <span>Break the grid, create custom layouts</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-green-500 mt-1">✓</span>
                <span>Pixel-perfect spacing control</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-green-500 mt-1">✓</span>
                <span>Custom animations and interactions</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-green-500 mt-1">✓</span>
                <span>Build components from scratch</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-green-500 mt-1">✓</span>
                <span>Figma-to-Webflow import</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-green-500 mt-1">✓</span>
                <span>CMS for dynamic content</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-red-500 mt-1">✗</span>
                <span>Can make ugly sites if you're not skilled</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white p-4 border-2 border-gray-200">
            <h3 class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Squarespace: Smart Constraints</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-green-500 mt-1">✓</span>
                <span>Beautiful templates (can't make ugly)</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-green-500 mt-1">✓</span>
                <span>Consistent design system</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-green-500 mt-1">✓</span>
                <span>Professional image treatment</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-green-500 mt-1">✓</span>
                <span>Built-in blogging platform</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-green-500 mt-1">✓</span>
                <span>E-commerce included</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-green-500 mt-1">✓</span>
                <span>Everything works together</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-red-500 mt-1">✗</span>
                <span>Limited to template structure</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-purple-100 p-4 border-l-[4px] border-purple-500">
          <p class="text-sm text-purple-900 font-medium">
            <strong>The insight:</strong> Webflow is like Figma—total freedom, requires skill. Squarespace is like Canva—constrained, but good outcomes guaranteed. 90% of designers don't need Webflow's power. They need Squarespace's beauty.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- CMS COMPARISON -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6">CMS & Blogging: Power vs Simplicity</h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="border-[3px] border-indigo-300 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Webflow CMS</h3>
          <div class="space-y-3 text-sm">
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              <strong>Power:</strong> 10/10
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              <strong>What you can do:</strong>
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600 ml-4">
              <li>• Custom content models (any structure)</li>
              <li>• Dynamic content binding</li>
              <li>• Filtering, sorting, search</li>
              <li>• Multi-item references</li>
              <li>• Collection pages with pagination</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="bg-indigo-50 p-3 border-l-[4px] border-indigo-500 mt-4">
              <p class="text-gray-800">
                <strong>Best for:</strong> Content-heavy sites with complex needs (job boards, directories, publications)
              </p>
            </div>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mt-2 text-xs">
              <strong>Downside:</strong> Overkill for simple blogs. Steep learning curve.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="border-[3px] border-teal-300 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Squarespace Blogging</h3>
          <div class="space-y-3 text-sm">
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              <strong>Power:</strong> 6/10
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              <strong>What you can do:</strong>
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600 ml-4">
              <li>• Blog posts with categories/tags</li>
              <li>• Comments (built-in)</li>
              <li>• RSS feed</li>
              <li>• Author profiles</li>
              <li>• Scheduled posts</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="bg-teal-50 p-3 border-l-[4px] border-teal-500 mt-4">
              <p class="text-gray-800">
                <strong>Best for:</strong> Simple blogs, portfolios, content marketing
              </p>
            </div>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mt-2 text-xs">
              <strong>Downside:</strong> Can't create custom content types. Limited filtering.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- PRICING BREAKDOWN -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6">Pricing: The Professional Premium</h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="border-[3px] border-indigo-300 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Webflow Pricing</h3>
          <div class="space-y-3 text-sm">
            <div class="flex justify-between pb-2 border-b border-gray-200">
              <span class="font-medium">Basic</span>
              <span class="text-gray-600">$23/mo</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between pb-2 border-b border-gray-200">
              <span class="font-medium">CMS</span>
              <span class="text-gray-600">$29/mo</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between pb-2 border-b border-gray-200">
              <span class="font-medium">Business</span>
              <span class="text-gray-600">$49/mo</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between">
              <span class="font-medium">Enterprise (with code export)</span>
              <span class="text-gray-600">$212/mo</span>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-indigo-50 p-3 border-l-[4px] border-indigo-500 mt-4">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900 text-xs">
                Scales with traffic. Popular sites cost $100-200+/mo.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="border-[3px] border-teal-300 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Squarespace Pricing</h3>
          <div class="space-y-3 text-sm">
            <div class="flex justify-between pb-2 border-b border-gray-200">
              <span class="font-medium">Personal</span>
              <span class="text-gray-600">$16/mo</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between pb-2 border-b border-gray-200">
              <span class="font-medium">Business (best value)</span>
              <span class="text-gray-600">$23/mo</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between pb-2 border-b border-gray-200">
              <span class="font-medium">Commerce (basic)</span>
              <span class="text-gray-600">$27/mo</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between">
              <span class="font-medium">Commerce (advanced)</span>
              <span class="text-gray-600">$49/mo</span>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-teal-50 p-3 border-l-[4px] border-teal-500 mt-4">
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900 text-xs">
                All-inclusive. No scaling fees. Bandwidth unlimited.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- WHEN EACH WINS -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6">When Each Platform Wins</h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <!-- WEBFLOW WINS -->
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-indigo-50 to-blue-50 border-[3px] border-indigo-300 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Choose Webflow If...</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
              <span class="text-indigo-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>You're a <strong>designer who wants total control</strong></span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
              <span class="text-indigo-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>You need <strong>custom animations and interactions</strong></span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
              <span class="text-indigo-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>You're building <strong>complex content sites</strong> (CMS power)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
              <span class="text-indigo-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>You want to <strong>export your code</strong></span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
              <span class="text-indigo-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>You're building <strong>client sites</strong> (agencies love Webflow)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
              <span class="text-indigo-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>You're willing to <strong>invest 2-3 weeks learning</strong></span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- SQUARESPACE WINS -->
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-teal-50 to-cyan-50 border-[3px] border-teal-300 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">Choose Squarespace If...</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
              <span class="text-teal-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>You want a <strong>professional site fast</strong> (hours, not days)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
              <span class="text-teal-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>You love <strong>Squarespace templates</strong> and don't need to customize heavily</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
              <span class="text-teal-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>You need <strong>e-commerce</strong> (included, no plugins)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
              <span class="text-teal-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>You want <strong>simple blogging</strong></span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
              <span class="text-teal-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>You don't want to <strong>learn a complex tool</strong></span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
              <span class="text-teal-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>You value <strong>simplicity over power</strong></span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- FINAL VERDICT -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-gray-900 p-6 md:p-8 text-white">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black mb-6">Final Verdict: The Designer's Choice</h2>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <p class="text-gray-300">
            After 19 hours of testing (14 Webflow, 5 Squarespace), here's the truth:
          </p>

          <div class="bg-indigo-900/50 border-l-[4px] border-indigo-500 p-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-indigo-100 font-medium">
              <strong>Webflow is for professional designers.</strong> If you make money building websites, Webflow is a superpower. The learning curve pays off in billable hours. You can charge $5,000+ for sites that take 4 days.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-teal-900/50 border-l-[4px] border-teal-500 p-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-teal-100 font-medium">
              <strong>Squarespace is for everyone else.</strong> If you're a photographer, consultant, small business, or creative who needs a portfolio—Squarespace delivers professional results in hours, not weeks. The constraints are features, not bugs.
            </p>
          </div>

          <p class="text-gray-300 mt-6">
            <strong>The brutal truth:</strong> 90% of people reading this comparison should use Squarespace. It's faster, easier, and the results are beautiful. Webflow is for the 10% who need pixel-perfect control and are willing to earn it.
          </p>

          <p class="text-gray-300">
            <strong>My recommendation:</strong> Start with Squarespace. If you hit its limits (rare), then learn Webflow. Don't start with Webflow unless you know you need its power.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

